â”‚                      â”‚                â”‚ structured output        â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ Ingredient Sub       â”‚ Gemini Flash   â”‚ Fast, simple task        â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ Recipe Chat          â”‚ Gemini Flash   â”‚ Conversational, quick    â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ Image Recognition    â”‚ Gemini Vision  â”‚ Multimodal capability    â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ OCR (Cookbook Scan)  â”‚ Gemini Vision  â”‚ Handles handwriting,     â”‚
â”‚                      â”‚                â”‚ interprets context       â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¼â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚ Recipe Import (URL)  â”‚ Gemini Flash   â”‚ Structured extraction    â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜

8.2 PROMPT ENGINEERING TEMPLATES
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

RECIPE GENERATION PROMPT:
```
You are a professional chef creating a recipe for a home cook.

INGREDIENTS AVAILABLE:
{ingredientsList}

CONSTRAINTS:
- Time: {timeLimit} minutes max
- Servings: {servings}
- Cuisine preference: {cuisine}
- Dietary restrictions: {dietary}

Generate a complete recipe in the following JSON format:
{
  "title": "Creative, appetizing name",
  "description": "One-sentence hook that makes you want to cook this",
  "cookTime": number (minutes),
  "prepTime": number (minutes),
  "servings": number,
  "difficulty": "Easy" | "Medium" | "Hard",
  "ingredients": [
    {
      "item": "ingredient name",
      "quantity": "amount",
      "unit": "measurement",
      "section": "Marinade" | "Sauce" | null
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    {
      "step": number,
      "instruction": "Clear, actionable step",
      "time": number | null (if timing matters),
      "tip": "Optional pro tip" | null
    }
  ],
  "nutrition": {
    "calories": number,
    "protein": number,
    "carbs": number,
    "fat": number
  },
  "tags": ["tag1", "tag2"]
}

RULES:
1. Only use provided ingredients (+ common pantry staples)
2. Be creative but practical
3. Include exact measurements
4. Make instructions beginner-friendly
5. Suggest plating/serving ideas in final step
```

SUBSTITUTION PROMPT:
```
You are a culinary expert helping find ingredient substitutions.

RECIPE CONTEXT:
- Dish: {recipeName}
- Original ingredient: {originalIngredient}
- Quantity needed: {quantity}
- Cooking method: {method} (e.g., baking, sautÃ©ing)
- Role in recipe: {role} (e.g., binding, moisture, flavor)

USER CONSTRAINT:
{constraint} (e.g., "Vegan", "Nut allergy", "Don't have it")

Provide 2-3 substitutes in JSON:
{
  "substitutes": [
    {
      "name": "Substitute ingredient",
      "quantity": "Adjusted amount if different",
      "reasoning": "Why this works chemically/culinarily",
      "tradeoffs": "What changes (taste, texture, color)",
      "preparation": "Any special prep needed",
      "confidence": "high" | "medium" | "low"
    }
  ]
}

Rank by best match first. Be honest about tradeoffs.
```

CHAT PROMPT (System):
```
You are a sous chef assistant in Culinara, helping a home cook
with the recipe below. The cook may be actively cooking right now,
so responses must be:
- CONCISE (2-3 sentences unless more detail explicitly needed)
- PRACTICAL (actionable advice, not theory)
- SAFE (warn about food safety when relevant)
- CONTEXTUAL (reference specific steps/ingredients from THIS recipe)

RECIPE LOADED:
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
{fullRecipeDetails}
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

If the user asks something unrelated to this recipe, politely
redirect: "I'm focused on helping with this specific recipe.
For other cooking questions, try creating a new chat from the
home screen!"

If asked about substitutions, provide 1-2 quick suggestions but
recommend using the "Magic Sub" button for detailed analysis.
```

8.3 RESPONSE STREAMING
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

For chat and recipe generation, stream responses for real-time feel:

```typescript
async function streamRecipeGeneration(ingredients: string[]) {
  const response = await ai.streamText({
    model: 'gemini-2.0-pro',
    prompt: generateRecipePrompt(ingredients),
  })

  for await (const chunk of response.textStream) {
    // Update UI incrementally
    updateRecipePreview(chunk)
  }
}
```

BENEFITS:
â€¢ Perceived speed: Users see progress immediately
â€¢ Engagement: Keeps attention during 5-10 second generation
â€¢ Transparency: Shows AI "thinking" process

8.4 ERROR HANDLING & FALLBACKS
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

AI REQUEST LIFECYCLE:
1. User initiates AI action
2. Show loading state immediately
3. Send request to Edge Function (proxy to Gemini)
4. If timeout (>10s) â†’ Show "Taking longer than expected..." message
5. If error â†’ Show friendly message + retry button
6. If success â†’ Smoothly transition to result

ERROR MESSAGES:
```typescript
const AI_ERROR_MESSAGES = {
  timeout: "The AI is taking a coffee break â˜• Try again?",
  rate_limit: "Too many cooks in the kitchen! Try again in a moment.",
  invalid_input: "Hmm, I need a bit more info. Can you add more details?",
  generic: "Something went wrong. Mind trying that again?"
}
```

GRACEFUL DEGRADATION:
â€¢ If AI unavailable â†’ Disable AI features, core app still works
â€¢ If vision API fails â†’ Allow manual ingredient entry
â€¢ If chat fails â†’ Show FAQ/tips instead

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
9. DATA MODELS & SCHEMA
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

9.1 DATABASE SCHEMA (PostgreSQL via Supabase)
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

```sql
-- Users table (managed by Supabase Auth)
CREATE TABLE profiles (
  id UUID REFERENCES auth.users PRIMARY KEY,
  username TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  display_name TEXT,
  bio TEXT,
  avatar_url TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Recipes table
CREATE TABLE recipes (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  image_url TEXT,
  cook_time INTEGER, -- minutes
  prep_time INTEGER, -- minutes
  servings INTEGER,
  difficulty TEXT CHECK (difficulty IN ('Easy', 'Medium', 'Hard')),
  cuisine TEXT,
  is_public BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  source_type TEXT CHECK (source_type IN ('original', 'ai_generated', 'imported', 'ocr')),
  source_url TEXT, -- if imported
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),

  -- Full-text search
  search_vector TSVECTOR GENERATED ALWAYS AS (
    to_tsvector('english', title || ' ' || COALESCE(description, ''))
  ) STORED
);

-- Ingredients table (many-to-many with recipes)
CREATE TABLE recipe_ingredients (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  item TEXT NOT NULL,
  quantity NUMERIC,
  unit TEXT,
  section TEXT, -- e.g., "Marinade", "Sauce"
  order_index INTEGER
);

-- Instructions table
CREATE TABLE recipe_instructions (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  step_number INTEGER NOT NULL,
  instruction TEXT NOT NULL,
  time_minutes INTEGER, -- if step has specific timing
  tip TEXT,
  order_index INTEGER
);

-- Tags (for categorization)
CREATE TABLE tags (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  name TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  category TEXT -- 'meal_type', 'dietary', 'cuisine', etc.
);

CREATE TABLE recipe_tags (
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  tag_id UUID REFERENCES tags(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  PRIMARY KEY (recipe_id, tag_id)
);

-- Likes
CREATE TABLE recipe_likes (
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, recipe_id)
);

-- Saves/Bookmarks
CREATE TABLE recipe_saves (
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  collection_id UUID REFERENCES collections(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, recipe_id)
);

-- Collections (user-organized recipe groups)
CREATE TABLE collections (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  is_public BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Follows (social graph)
CREATE TABLE follows (
  follower_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  following_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (follower_id, following_id),
  CHECK (follower_id != following_id)
);

-- Comments
CREATE TABLE comments (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  parent_id UUID REFERENCES comments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE, -- for nested replies
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Chat history (for Sous Chef conversations)
CREATE TABLE chat_messages (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  recipe_id UUID REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  role TEXT CHECK (role IN ('user', 'assistant')),
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Nutrition data (optional, linked to recipes)
CREATE TABLE recipe_nutrition (
  recipe_id UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES recipes(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  calories INTEGER,
  protein_g NUMERIC,
  carbs_g NUMERIC,
  fat_g NUMERIC,
  fiber_g NUMERIC,
  sugar_g NUMERIC,
  sodium_mg NUMERIC
);

-- Indexes for performance
CREATE INDEX idx_recipes_user_id ON recipes(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_recipes_is_public ON recipes(is_public);
CREATE INDEX idx_recipes_created_at ON recipes(created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_recipes_search ON recipes USING GIN(search_vector);
CREATE INDEX idx_recipe_likes_recipe_id ON recipe_likes(recipe_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_follows_following ON follows(following_id);
```

9.2 ROW LEVEL SECURITY (RLS) POLICIES
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

```sql
-- Enable RLS
ALTER TABLE recipes ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
-- ... (enable for all tables)

-- Recipes: Users can read public recipes or their own
CREATE POLICY "Public recipes are viewable by everyone"
  ON recipes FOR SELECT
  USING (is_public = true);

CREATE POLICY "Users can view their own recipes"
  ON recipes FOR SELECT
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Users can insert their own recipes
CREATE POLICY "Users can create recipes"
  ON recipes FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Users can update their own recipes
CREATE POLICY "Users can update own recipes"
  ON recipes FOR UPDATE
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Users can delete their own recipes
CREATE POLICY "Users can delete own recipes"
  ON recipes FOR DELETE
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Likes: Anyone can like public recipes
CREATE POLICY "Users can like public recipes"
  ON recipe_likes FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (
    EXISTS (
      SELECT 1 FROM recipes
      WHERE id = recipe_id AND is_public = true
    )
  );
```

9.3 TYPESCRIPT TYPES
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

```typescript
// src/types/recipe.ts

export interface User {
  id: string
  username: string
  displayName: string | null
  bio: string | null
  avatarUrl: string | null
  createdAt: string
}

export interface Ingredient {
  id: string
  item: string
  quantity: number | null
  unit: string | null
  section: string | null
}

export interface Instruction {
  id: string
  stepNumber: number
  instruction: string
  timeMinutes: number | null
  tip: string | null
}

export interface Recipe {
  id: string
  userId: string
  author?: User // Joined data
  title: string
  description: string | null
  imageUrl: string | null
  cookTime: number
  prepTime: number
  servings: number
  difficulty: 'Easy' | 'Medium' | 'Hard'
  cuisine: string | null
  isPublic: boolean
  sourceType: 'original' | 'ai_generated' | 'imported' | 'ocr'
  sourceUrl: string | null
  ingredients: Ingredient[]
  instructions: Instruction[]
  nutrition?: Nutrition
  tags: Tag[]
  likesCount: number
  isLiked: boolean // Computed based on current user
  isSaved: boolean // Computed based on current user
  createdAt: string
  updatedAt: string
}

export interface Nutrition {
  calories: number
  proteinG: number
  carbsG: number
  fatG: number
  fiberG: number | null
  sugarG: number | null
  sodiumMg: number | null
}

export interface Tag {
  id: string
  name: string
  category: string
}

export interface Collection {
  id: string
  userId: string
  name: string
  description: string | null
  isPublic: boolean
  recipeCount: number
  createdAt: string
}

export interface ChatMessage {
  id: string
  role: 'user' | 'assistant'
  content: string
  createdAt: string
}
```

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
10. SUCCESS METRICS & KPIs
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

10.1 NORTH STAR METRIC
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

**Weekly Active Recipe Interactions (WARI)**
= Unique users who create, view, or interact with recipes weekly

This metric captures core value: helping people cook.

10.2 PRIMARY METRICS
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

ACQUISITION:
â€¢ New user signups per week
â€¢ Signup source attribution (organic, referral, social)
â€¢ Signupâ†’First recipe time (goal: <2 minutes)

ENGAGEMENT:
â€¢ Daily Active Users (DAU) / Weekly Active Users (WAU)
â€¢ Average recipes created per user per month
â€¢ AI interactions per session (goal: 5+)
â€¢ Chat messages sent per recipe view
â€¢ Substitution requests per recipe
â€¢ Time spent in app per session (goal: 10+ min)

RETENTION:
â€¢ Day 1, Day 7, Day 30 retention rates (goal: 60%, 40%, 25%)
â€¢ Weekly recipe creation streak (gamification metric)
â€¢ Recipes cooked per month (self-reported or inferred from views)

SOCIAL/VIRAL:
â€¢ Public recipe publish rate (% of recipes made public)
â€¢ Average likes per public recipe
â€¢ Recipe shares (external + internal)
â€¢ Follower growth rate
â€¢ Recipe "forks" (community remixing)

AI-SPECIFIC:
â€¢ AI generation success rate (user keeps vs. regenerates)
â€¢ Substitution acceptance rate
â€¢ Chat satisfaction (thumbs up/down)
â€¢ OCR accuracy (% requiring manual correction)

10.3 ANALYTICS IMPLEMENTATION
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

TOOLS:
â€¢ PostHog: Product analytics, session replay, feature flags
â€¢ Sentry: Error tracking, performance monitoring
â€¢ Google Analytics: Traffic sources, SEO performance

KEY EVENTS TO TRACK:
```typescript
// User actions
analytics.track('recipe_viewed', { recipeId, source: 'feed' })
analytics.track('recipe_created', { method: 'ai_generated', timeToCreate })
analytics.track('ingredient_substituted', { originalIngredient, reason })
analytics.track('chat_message_sent', { recipeId, messageLength })
analytics.track('recipe_shared', { platform: 'instagram' })

// AI performance
analytics.track('ai_generation_started', { ingredientCount })
analytics.track('ai_generation_completed', { duration, success })
analytics.track('ai_substitution_requested', { ingredient, constraint })
analytics.track('ai_chat_response', { responseTime, tokenCount })

// Funnel events
analytics.track('signup_started')
analytics.track('signup_completed', { method: 'google' })
analytics.track('first_recipe_created', { timeSinceSignup })
analytics.track('first_recipe_cooked', { timeSinceCreation })
```

10.4 A/B TESTING FRAMEWORK
